      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Windows 10 offers two models for work-owned devices for accessing work resources:",
      "pos": [
        3849,
        3930
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure AD Join",
      "pos": [
        3935,
        3948
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Domain Join.",
      "pos": [
        3951,
        3963
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Both are valid options depending on the organization needs and requirements.",
      "pos": [
        3966,
        4042
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In some cases, organizations might benefit from enabling both methods of deployment.",
      "pos": [
        4043,
        4127
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When to use Azure Active Directory Join",
      "pos": [
        4132,
        4171
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure AD Join is a new self-service work provisioning experience in Windows 10.",
      "pos": [
        4173,
        4252
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It is targeted for the workers who primarily access work resources in the cloud such as Office 365.",
      "pos": [
        4254,
        4353
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It is a lightweight way to configure PCs, tablets and phones for the enterprise.",
      "pos": [
        4354,
        4434
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Devices are managed via MDM using consistent controls across Windows platforms.",
      "pos": [
        4435,
        4514
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        4516,
        4563
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Use Azure AD Join for any of these reasons<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>:"
    },
    {
      "content": "You want to enable self-service provisioning of devices for workers on-the-go.",
      "pos": [
        4569,
        4647
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You provide users with work-owned mobile devices like tablets and phones.",
      "pos": [
        4652,
        4725
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You want to manage a set of users in Azure AD instead of AD, such as seasonal workers, contractors, or students.",
      "pos": [
        4730,
        4842
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You want to provide joining capabilities to workers in remote branch offices with limited on-premises infrastructure.",
      "pos": [
        4847,
        4964
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You do not have on-premises AD.",
      "pos": [
        4969,
        5000
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Some organizations will use Azure AD Join as the primary way to deploy work-owned devices, especially as they migrate most or all of their resources to the cloud.",
      "pos": [
        5002,
        5164
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Hybrid organizations with both AD and Azure AD can also choose to deploy one method or another depending on the user or department.",
      "pos": [
        5165,
        5296
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "School districts and universities may manage staff in AD and manage students in Azure AD, or some companies might want remote offices or the sales department on Azure AD.",
      "pos": [
        5297,
        5467
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Both Azure AD Join and Domain Join methods can be used within a hybrid organization.",
      "pos": [
        5468,
        5552
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure AD Join can be a great complement for deploying devices in a work environment.",
      "pos": [
        5553,
        5637
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        5640,
        5747
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>If most access to enterprise resources is via the cloud, an organization may enjoy additional benefits<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>:"
    },
    {
      "content": "You may be able to remove dependencies on on-premises identity infrastructure.",
      "pos": [
        5751,
        5829
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can simplify your devices deployment model by getting away from imaging solutions by allowing self-service configuration.",
      "pos": [
        5832,
        5957
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can use MDM to manage all your devices across different platforms.",
      "pos": [
        5960,
        6030
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6032,
        6215
      ],
      "content": "For more information about Azure AD Join please see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Extending cloud capabilities to Windows 10 devices through Azure Active Directory Join<ept id=\"p1\">](active-directory-azureadjoin-overview.md)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "When to use Domain Join (or keep using it)",
      "pos": [
        6220,
        6262
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Domain join is the traditional way organizations have connected devices for work for the last 15 years and more.",
      "pos": [
        6264,
        6376
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It has enabled users to sign-in to their devices using their AD work accounts and allowed IT to centrally and fully manage these devices.",
      "pos": [
        6377,
        6514
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Organizations typically rely on imaging methods to provision devices and generally use System Center Configuration Manager (SCCM) or Group Policy to manage them.",
      "pos": [
        6515,
        6676
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6678,
        6752
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>You would use domain join in your enterprise for any of these reasons<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>:"
    },
    {
      "content": "You have Win32 apps deployed to these devices that use NTLM/Kerberos.",
      "pos": [
        6756,
        6825
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You require GP or SCCM/DCM to manage devices.",
      "pos": [
        6828,
        6873
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You want to continue to use imaging solutions to configure devices for your employees.",
      "pos": [
        6876,
        6962
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6964,
        7071
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Domain Join in Windows 10 will also gives you the following benefits after being connected to Azure AD<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>:"
    },
    {
      "content": "Strong device-bound authentication and convenient sign-in for work account with Microsoft Passport and Windows Hello.",
      "pos": [
        7075,
        7192
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Access to enterprise Windows Store using work accounts (no Microsoft account required).",
      "pos": [
        7195,
        7282
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Enterprise compliant roaming of user settings across devices using work account (no Microsoft account required).",
      "pos": [
        7285,
        7397
